use a real tokenizer matching the API's algorithm (e.g., OpenAI's tokenizer) to measure the prompt token count and verify it stays within budget.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.5,"System":0.3,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the API signals that the request rate is too high, the module waits and retries rather than returning an error to the caller.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"The retry logic itself (detection of rate-limit status, waiting, and retrying) is testable with a mocked API that returns a rate-limit error on the first call and succeeds on the second. The wait behavior can be verified by mocking `time.sleep` or using a time-mocking library (e.g., freezegun) to test without actual delays. The failure (module returns error immediately instead of retrying) is caught by the mock sequence. Real wait times and backoff algorithms can be validated at System level, but the minimum to catch the core failure is Unit.","test_description":"Mock the external API to raise a rate-limit exception (or return HTTP 429) on the first call and succeed on the second call. Mock time.sleep to avoid real waiting. Call classify(document) and verify: (1) the method does not raise an exception, (2) the result is valid, and (3) the mocked API was called at least twice. Optionally verify the wait duration by checking sleep() was called with appropriate backoff.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.7,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13501,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13501},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8dbc26ca-214f-44e5-b9aa-212edcc8e3f1","uuid":"9